<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=121215">East Cabilis</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>The Footman Pike</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    The Footman Pike</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=124987"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:jmgabris@eos.ncsu.edu">Nevunak</a> | 
		                        9/6/2000 6:22:45 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Here is the info on the Footman's Pike.  To get the directions on crafting one, go to the Weaponsmith at the warrior's guild and say &quot;Tell me how to make the Footman Pike&quot;<BR>
To create the Footman's Pike, you will need the following items:<BR>
<BR>
An Iron Rod<BR>
A Forging Hammer<BR>
A Footman's Pike head<BR>
In order to create the pike head, you need:<BR>
Geozite Tool<BR>
A Pike Head<BR>
Petrified Redwood<BR>
<BR>
The rod, hammer, and pike head can all be bought from the Weaponsmith.<BR>
Petrified Redwood can be foraged in Warslik's Woods.<BR>
<BR>
To make the pike, first place the pike head, the tool, and the redwood in the forge. You do NOT need the plans given from completing the Footman Pike quest (the one with the Goblin and Froglok javelins).  Good news for you folk who lost your pike and can't complete the quest.<BR>
Then, place the Footman Pike head you just created into the forge, with the rod and forging hammer.  NO water, NO plans.<BR>
The pike head apparently requires no smithing skill to make.  However, when I first attempted to make the pike itself, I failed through lack of skill.  I trained 20 points into smithing (all I had at the time) and then went back to create the pike...and hey presto it was trivial.<BR>
<BR>
Again, the plans are NOT necessary to make this pike...a friend successfully created his even though he never turned in his guild note and got his Partisan Pike.<BR>
Now, if anyone has any information on the Memory of Sebilis, apparently for the next Pike quest....well that'd be just peachy :)<BR>
<BR>
Nevunak<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
UPDATE<BR>
--------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
   Greetings!!   Just today - 06 September 2000, I completed the Iksar Warrior Footman's Pike quest.  It has been 'fixed' so that you can no longer do it the way you have it posted.  You can no longer skip the quest for the Footman Pike plans.  Also, the instructions from Weaponsmith Grugle have changed, but are kind of misleading.  The important changes are as follows:<BR>
 <BR>
You MUST complete Drill Master Kyg's quest to fill the footman's pack with javelins.  (this was not so once upon a time)<BR>
 <BR>
When you talk to Weaponsmith Grugle about the footman's pike, his instructions for forging the Pike head now say &quot;To forge the pike head you will need a geozite tool, raw pike head, and petrified redwood if the footman pike head plans are yours.&quot;  Of course this doesn't tell you whether you only need to HAVE the pike head plans, or you need to include them in the forge.  They must be included in the forge, along with the other three items.<BR>
 <BR>
There appear to be 'skill checks' on both forging operations.  Both were 'trivial' to me at level-51 blacksmithing skill.<BR>
When you forge the pike head, the Geozite Tool is returned along with the Pike head.  When you forge the Pike, the forging hammer is returned along with the pike.<BR>
                         Dadathius,  Povar<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
