	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   Greetings!!   Just today - 06 September 2000, I completed the Iksar Warrior Footman's Pike quest.  It has been 'fixed' so that you can no longer skip the quest for the Footman Pike plans.  Also, the instructions from Weaponsmith Grugle have changed, but are kind of misleading.  The important changes are as follows:<BR>
<BR>
You MUST complete Drill Master Kyg's quest to fill the footman's pack with javelins.  (this was not so once upon a time)<BR>
<BR>
When you talk to Weaponsmith Grugle about the footman's pike, his instructions for forging the Pike head now say &quot;To forge the pike head you will need a geozite tool, raw pike head, and petrified redwood if the footman pike head plans are yours.&quot;  Of course this doesn't tell you whether you only need to HAVE the pike head plans, or you need to include them in the forge.  They must be included in the forge, along with the other three items.<BR>
<BR>
There appear to be 'skill checks' on both forging operations.  Both were 'trivial' to me at level-51 blacksmithing skill.<BR>
When you forge the pike head, the Geozite Tool is returned along with the Pike head.  When you forge the Pike, the forging hammer is returned along with the Pike.<BR>
                         Dadathius,  Povar
				</font>
